                  <birth when="1883"/>
                  
                  <floruit notBefore="1914" notAfter="1970">He was an outstanding church scholar, 
                     administrator and the first Ethiopian Patriarch. 
                     He was ordained priest in <date>1914</date>. 
                     In <date>1934</date>, he was made <persName ref="PRS2533Baselyos">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾǝč̣č̣age</roleName>
                  </persName>
                     
                     becoming the 59th abbot of <placeName ref="INS0341DL"/>. 
                     During the Italian invasion he was in exile in <placeName ref="wd:Q1218"/> and 
                     later after the liberation he returned back to Ethiopia. In <date>1949</date>, he was consecrated as a bishop in <placeName ref="wd:Q87"/>.
                     In <date>1956</date>, following the death of <persName ref="PRS8033Qerellos"/> 
                     <persName ref="PRS2533Baselyos">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾabuna</roleName> 
                        Bāsǝlyos </persName>
                     became the first Patriarch of the Ethiopian Orthodox Tawāḥǝdo Church. </floruit> 
                  
               <death when="1970">He died at <placeName ref="LOC1216AddisA"/> in <date>1970</date>. </death>
               </person>
